Package: phenoQC
Title: Automated Phenotypic Data Quality Control for Plant Breeding Trials
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Joash Joshua", "Ayo", , "joash.ayo@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0000-0000-0000"))
Description: Provides automated, reproducible quality control for phenotypic 
    data from plant breeding field trials. Includes trial structure validation 
    (duplicate plots, missing entries, replication balance), statistical and 
    spatial outlier detection, spatial trend diagnostics, missing data analysis 
    with spatial imputation, and automated HTML QC report generation. All 
    functions are pipe-friendly and non-interactive, designed for scripting 
    and batch processing. Integrates seamlessly with 'brapiR2' for end-to-end 
    breeding data pipelines.
